Everything “Yagels” (Greek Yogurt Bagels)

You only need a few ingredients!

By Kate MerkerPublished: May 4, 2025
Be the first to review!
Jump to recipe
Yields:
4 serving(s)
Total Time:
45 mins
Cal/Serv:
216

No “knead” to wake up early to make these “yagels”—they require no yeast and no rising time. The secret is Greek yogurt, which adds protein and a pleasant tang. Think sourdough flavor in a bagel.

Advertisement - Continue Reading Below

Ingredients

  • 1 cup

    self-rising flour, plus more for dusting 

  • 1 cup

    plain Greek yogurt 

  • 1

    large egg, beaten 

  • 1 1/2 Tbsp.

    everything bagel seasoning

You’ll Also Love:

Waffles With Spicy Glazed Bacon and Pecans

Chocolate-Zucchini Bran Muffins

Almond-Chia Energy Bites

Skillet Latke

Cashew Milk

Oatmeal with Apricots and Pistachios

Oatmeal with Yogurt and Toasted Almonds

Directions

    1. Step 1Heat oven to 350°F. Line baking sheet with parchment paper. 
    2. Step 2In medium bowl, stir together flour and yogurt until combined and dough starts to form (it will be very sticky). Turn out dough onto lightly floured work surface. 
    3. Step 3Knead 2 minutes, adding more flour as necessary, until dough is soft and only slightly sticky. Divide into 4 equal pieces and roll each into 11/4-inch-thick log (about 8 inches long); pinch ends of each log together to form bagels. Transfer to prepared baking sheet. 
    4. Step 4Brush tops of bagels with egg and sprinkle with everything bagel seasoning. Bake until golden brown, 28 to 35 minutes. Serve while still warm.

NUTRITIONAL INFORMATION (per serving): About 216 calories, 5.5 g fat (2 g saturated), 55 mg cholesterol, 527 mg sodium, 30 g carbohydrates, 1 g fiber, 3 g sugar (0 g added sugar), 11 g protein
